# Privacy Policy — BudgetBlock

**Last updated: April 2026**

## Overview

BudgetBlock is a Chrome extension that lets you set daily time budgets for websites. This policy explains how the extension handles your data.

## Data Collected

BudgetBlock stores the following data **locally in your browser only**:

- The list of sites you have configured, including their domains, daily budgets, and block style preferences
- Daily usage data per domain (time spent in milliseconds) for the last 7 days

This data is used solely to enforce your time budgets and display usage in the extension popup.

## Data Storage

- Site settings are stored using Chrome's `storage.sync` API, which may sync across your Chrome profile if you are signed in to Chrome with sync enabled
- Usage data is stored using Chrome's `storage.local` API and stays on the current device

No data is transmitted to any external server or third party.

## Data Sharing

No data is collected, transmitted, or shared with any external server, service, or third party.

## Permissions

- **storage** — used to save site settings and usage data
- **alarms** — used to update the badge counter every minute and trigger the midnight usage reset
- **tabs** — used to track which tab is active in order to measure time spent on configured sites
- **windows** — used to detect when Chrome loses focus so the timer can be paused
- **host_permissions (`<all_urls>`)** — required to run the content script on every page so budget enforcement can work on any site you configure

